TIGER MORTALITY, ZOO - CHINA (03)
=================================
[see
Tiger mortality, zoo - China 970502145708
Tiger mortality, zoo - China (02) 970502200739]
[1]
Date: Fri, 2 May 1997 14:32:09 -0700 (PDT)
From: brideout@sunstroke.sdsu.edu (Bruce Rideout)
Canine distemper virus has caused mortality on both captive and free-ranging
large cats, but without more specific information from the Chinese regarding
these cases, all we can do is speculate, which doesn't get us very far.
